<!--
    Demo Case 04 - Pending / General Inquiry / High priority
    ====================================================================

    Synthetic seed record for the case-management POC scoped application.
    This file is the FOURTH of the 10-case demo dataset; together with
    cases 01 through 03 and cases 05 through 10, it satisfies the AAP
    requirement (Section 0.7.4) of "at least 10 demo cases across all
    six statuses and both case types," and contributes to the dataset
    matrix:

        Case 01 - Draft       / General Inquiry
        Case 02 - Open        / General Inquiry
        Case 03 - In Progress / General Inquiry
        Case 04 - Pending     / General Inquiry / High        ## THIS FILE
        Case 05 - Resolved    / General Inquiry
        Case 06 - Closed      / General Inquiry
        Case 07 - Open        / Complaint
        Case 08 - In Progress / Complaint
        Case 09 - Resolved    / Complaint
        Case 10 - Closed      / Complaint

    The 10-case dataset thus exercises:
      * Every one of the six statuses (Draft, Open, In Progress, Pending,
        Resolved, Closed) - this case occupies the PENDING slot and is
        the ONLY Pending case in the entire 10-case dataset, making it
        the canonical Pending-status test case for the POC
      * Both case types (General Inquiry and Complaint) across the
        full lifecycle - case 04 occupies the General Inquiry side
        of the Pending status; the Complaint side of the Pending
        status is intentionally not represented in the 10-case set
        because the Pending semantics are case-type-agnostic and the
        General Inquiry coverage suffices for Validation Gate 2's
        Pending transition tests
      * Multiple priorities (Low, Medium, High, Critical) - this case
        contributes to one of the High bars in the all_cases_by_priority
        chart (paired with cases 07 and 09, which are also High)
      * The polymorphic case_party UI Policy (Person branch via the
        seed script's witness party referencing the demo agent)
      * The Pending status's MANDATORY pending_reason field (set to
        "Awaiting Info" per AAP Section 0.5.5 and the agent prompt's
        Rule 5)

    Lifecycle position - WHY Pending / General Inquiry / High is
    meaningful:
      A General Inquiry case that has reached Pending status has
      traversed:
        Draft -> Open -> In Progress -> Pending
      The agent has been actively investigating the case (In Progress)
      but has had to pause work because external information is needed
      from the requester or another party. Per AAP Section 0.5.5's
      transition matrix:
        - The In Progress -> Pending transition is unconditional but
          REQUIRES pending_reason to be populated (set by the Flow
          Designer subflow validate_pending_transition.xml from a
          prompt to the caller; one of "Awaiting Info", "Awaiting
          Third Party", or "Other")
        - The Pending -> In Progress transition is also unconditional
          and CLEARS pending_reason via the
          clear_pending_reason_on_inprogress business rule
      This case occupies the Pending side of that pair: pending_reason
      is populated with "Awaiting Info" (the most common cause - the
      agent is awaiting clarifying information from the requester).
      The High priority is appropriate for the Pending status: the
      case carries elevated urgency that has been temporarily paused;
      when the missing information arrives, the case will resume
      In Progress and move toward Resolved promptly.

    Role / cross-dependency context (per AAP Section 0.5.2):

      This case DEPENDS ON (loaded BEFORE this record):
        - The scoped application records under ../../app/
            (sys_app and sys_scope; this case's <sys_scope>/<sys_package>
             reference fields resolve via the source attribute against
             those records)
        - The case table definition at ../../tables/x_[scope]_case.xml
            (this record's <sys_class_name>x_[scope]_case</sys_class_name>
             requires the table to exist)
        - All dictionary entries for the case table under
            ../../dictionary/x_[scope]_case_*.xml  (every populated
            field below requires its dictionary entry to be present,
            INCLUDING the optional pending_reason dictionary entry at
            ../../dictionary/x_[scope]_case_pending_reason.xml)
        - All choice records under ../../choices/  (the type=General
            Inquiry, status=Pending, priority=High, AND
            pending_reason=Awaiting Info choice values must all be
            registered; the Awaiting Info choice is defined at
            ../../choices/sys_choice_case_pending_reason.xml as the
            FIRST choice value in alphabetical order alongside
            "Awaiting Third Party" and "Other")
        - The auto-numbering record at
            ../../numbers/sys_number_x_[scope]_case.xml  (defines the
            CASE0000001 format; this record's <number/> is intentionally
            absent so the platform auto-generates per that format on
            insert)
        - The role records under ../../roles/  (the demo agent's read
            and write access requires the x_[scope]_case_agent role
            and its ACLs)
        - The ACL records under ../../acl/  (table-level and field-level
            ACLs gate read/write access; the demo agent reads/writes
            this case via the "Assigned only" clause of the agent ACLs:
            assigned_agent = current.sys_id OR
            assigned_group IN current.user_group_membership)
        - The business rule records under ../../business_rules/
            (set_opened_date Before-Insert auto-sets <opened_date> on
             this case at import time; block_draft_backtransition will
             prevent any Pending->Draft attempt;
             clear_pending_reason_on_inprogress will fire on the future
             Pending->In Progress transition and clear pending_reason -
             NOT on this insert; validate_assigned_agent_membership
             validates that the demo agent is a member of the demo team
             at insert time)
        - The flow records under ../../flows/
            (../../flows/general_inquiry_state_machine.xml governs this
             case type; the validate_pending_transition subflow at
             ../../flows/sub_flows/validate_pending_transition.xml is
             responsible for prompting the caller for pending_reason
             when an In Progress case is set to Pending. THIS CASE
             demonstrates the post-transition state where
             pending_reason has been populated)
        - ../users/sys_user_x_[scope]_demo_agent.xml  (referenced by
            <assigned_agent>; resolved by user_name lookup)
        - ../groups/sys_user_group_x_[scope]_demo_team.xml  (referenced
            by <assigned_group>; resolved by name lookup)
        - ../role_assignments/sys_user_has_role_x_[scope]_demo_agent.xml
            (grants the case_agent role to the demo agent so the agent
            can read/write this case via the "Assigned only" ACL clause)

      This case IS REFERENCED BY (loaded AFTER this record):
        - ../tasks/x_[scope]_case_task_demo_*.xml - specifically the
            Open task per the seed script's task table:
            "Demo task 03: Follow up with requester" (status = Open,
            due_date = +2 days). This task supports the Pending case
            semantics: the case is paused awaiting external info, but
            the agent still has an Open follow-up task tracked. The
            non-Closed task means the In Progress -> Resolved
            transition is currently BLOCKED for this case (just as it
            is for case 03), but unlike case 03 this case is in
            Pending not In Progress; the resolve attempt would only
            trigger after the case returns to In Progress and the
            task is closed.
        - ../parties/x_[scope]_case_party_demo_*.xml - specifically
            the Person-type Witness party referencing the demo agent.
            This exercises the Person branch of the polymorphic UI
            Policy on the case_party form (the
            x_[scope]_case_party_conditional_fields UI Policy shows
