        - The all_cases_by_status Manager View bar chart at
            ../../reports/x_[scope]_all_cases_by_status.xml  (this case
            populates the SOLE Pending bar, since it is the only
            Pending case in the dataset)
        - The all_cases_by_type Manager View donut at
            ../../reports/x_[scope]_all_cases_by_type.xml  (this case
            populates the General Inquiry slice)
        - The all_cases_by_priority Manager View bar chart at
            ../../reports/x_[scope]_all_cases_by_priority.xml  (this
            case populates one of the High entries alongside cases
            07 Open Complaint High and 09 Resolved Complaint High)
        - The case_count_by_status Agent Workspace donut at
            ../../reports/x_[scope]_case_count_by_status.xml  (this case
            populates the SOLE Pending slice, since it is the only
            Pending case in the dataset)
        - The cases_opened_30d Manager View single-score widget at
            ../../reports/x_[scope]_cases_opened_30d.xml  (since
            opened_date is auto-set to "now" by the set_opened_date
            business rule at insert time, this case is included in the
            count of cases opened within the last 30 days)
        - The avg_time_to_close Manager View single-score widget at
            ../../reports/x_[scope]_avg_time_to_close.xml  (this case
            does NOT contribute because the widget filters on
            status=Closed and this case is Pending, not Closed; only
            cases 06 and 10 contribute to the average)
        - The validate_pending_transition subflow test in Validation
            Gate 2 (PENDING-SET): this case demonstrates the
            POST-TRANSITION state where pending_reason has been
            populated to "Awaiting Info". The pre-transition state is
            tested by sibling case 03 (In Progress) - if a case_agent
            sets case 03 to Pending via the form, the
            validate_pending_transition subflow prompts for
            pending_reason and persists the chosen value (one of
            "Awaiting Info", "Awaiting Third Party", "Other").
        - The clear_pending_reason_on_inprogress business rule test
            in Validation Gate 2 (PENDING-CLEAR): if a case_agent
            sets THIS CASE back to In Progress via the form (the
            standard "info has arrived, resume work" path), the
            clear_pending_reason_on_inprogress Before-Update business
            rule fires and clears the pending_reason field
            (pending_reason -> null). The case status moves Pending
            -> In Progress without further validation.
        - The Agent Workspace's "My Open Cases" list at
            ../../reports/x_[scope]_my_open_cases.xml DOES include
            this case: the list filter is "status NOT IN (Resolved,
            Closed) AND assigned_agent = javascript:gs.getUserID()".
            Pending is NOT in the (Resolved, Closed) exclusion list,
            and the demo agent is the assigned_agent, so when the
            demo agent impersonates and views the dashboard this
            case appears in the list.

    Authoring rules honored (per AAP Sections 0.7.1 / 0.7.2 and the
    agent prompt's ten authoring rules):

      Rule 1 - Synthetic only (AAP Section 0.7.2 NO-PII clause):
        subject       = "Demo case 04: Pending (General Inquiry)"
        description   = "Synthetic Pending case awaiting external
                         info." (no PII; the wording emphasizes the
                         lifecycle position - paused awaiting info -
                         and complements the pending_reason value
                         "Awaiting Info" semantically)
        requester_name  = "Synthetic Requester Four" (synthetic
                          identifier using the literal word "Synthetic"
                          plus the SPELLED-OUT numeral "Four" for the
                          requester, NOT a real person's name;
                          consistent with the peer convention used by
                          cases 05 through 10 - SPELLED-OUT word for
                          the requester_name)
        requester_email = "requester-4@example.invalid"
                          (RFC 2606 / BCP 32 reserved .invalid TLD never
                          resolves to a real domain; the local part uses
                          the NUMERAL "4" matching the file numbering -
                          consistent with the peer convention used by
                          cases 05-10's NUMERAL convention for the email
                          local part versus the SPELLED-OUT word for
                          the requester_name field)

      Rule 2 - No auto-number override:
        The <number/> element is intentionally absent. The auto-number
        engine defined in ../../numbers/sys_number_x_[scope]_case.xml
        generates a CASE0000001-format value on insert per AAP Section
        0.5.7 (the "number" row of the case schema specifies "Auto-
        number" with format CASE0000001 and Read-only constraint).

      Rule 3 - Auto-set opened_date (NO explicit override):
        The <opened_date/> element is intentionally absent. The
        set_opened_date Before-Insert business rule at
        ../../business_rules/x_[scope]_set_opened_date.xml fires on
        insert and sets opened_date = gs.nowDateTime(). On a fresh
        PDI import this yields an opened_date "now," which is correct
        for this Pending case because:
          * It is NOT used to compute avg_time_to_close (which excludes
            non-Closed cases via the closed_date IS NOT NULL filter).
          * It IS appropriate for the case to appear "fresh" in the
            cases_opened_30d count (a paused-but-active case is still
            recently opened).
        Pattern matches case 05 (Resolved General Inquiry) and case
        09 (Resolved Complaint), which also do NOT need explicit
        opened_date overrides. Only cases 06 (Closed General Inquiry)
        and 10 (Closed Complaint) carry explicit opened_date and
        closed_date overrides because they are the only inputs to
        the avg_time_to_close widget.

      Rule 4 - No closed_date in Pending:
        The <closed_date/> element is intentionally absent. Per AAP
        Section 0.5.5 the set_closed_date business rule fires only on
        Resolved -> Closed update, NOT on direct insert with status =
        Pending. Pending cases by definition have not been Closed
        (Pending is an intermediate-pause state, not a terminal
        state), so closed_date MUST remain null. The
        avg_time_to_close report filters on status=Closed and ignores
        non-Closed records, so this case correctly does NOT appear
        in that widget.

      Rule 5 - Both assignments populated, MANDATORY pending_reason:
        assigned_group = "x_[scope]_demo_team"  (mandatory because the
                         case had to traverse Open -> ... -> Pending,
                         and assigned_group is required at Open per
                         AAP Section 0.5.5; the value persists through
                         all subsequent statuses including Pending)
        assigned_agent = "x_[scope]_demo_agent"  (mandatory because the
                         case had to traverse In Progress -> Pending,
                         and assigned_agent is required at In Progress
                         per AAP Section 0.5.5; the value persists
                         through Pending; the agent is also a member
                         of x_[scope]_demo_team per the seed script's
                         group-membership creation, satisfying the
                         validate_assigned_agent_membership business
                         rule's pre-update guard)
        pending_reason = "Awaiting Info"  (MANDATORY for Pending status
                         per AAP Section 0.5.5 and the agent prompt's
                         Rule 5/Rule 6; this is the canonical Pending
                         case for the "Awaiting Info" reason - the
                         agent is paused awaiting clarifying
                         information from the requester or another
                         party. The validate_pending_transition
                         subflow set this value when the case
                         transitioned from In Progress to Pending; the
                         value will be cleared by the
                         clear_pending_reason_on_inprogress business
                         rule when/if the case is set back to In
                         Progress)

      Rule 6 - Choice value precision:
        type           = "General Inquiry"  (exactly as registered in
                         ../../choices/sys_choice_case_type.xml; the
                         FIRST of the two case types; capital G and
                         capital I deliberate; the space between
                         "General" and "Inquiry" is a single ASCII
                         space, NOT an em-space or other Unicode
                         whitespace)
        status         = "Pending"     (exactly as registered in
                         ../../choices/sys_choice_case_status.xml;
                         capital P deliberate - "Pending" not
                         "pending" or "PENDING")
        priority       = "High"        (exactly as registered in
                         ../../choices/sys_choice_case_priority.xml;
                         capital H deliberate - "High" not "high" or
                         "HIGH")
        pending_reason = "Awaiting Info"  (exactly as registered in
                         ../../choices/sys_choice_case_pending_reason.xml;
                         capital A and capital I deliberate; the space
                         between "Awaiting" and "Info" is a single
                         ASCII space; the value is one of three
                         registered choices: "Awaiting Info",
                         "Awaiting Third Party", "Other" - this case
                         uses the first/most-common choice)

      Rule 7 - Zero hardcoded sys_id cross-references (AAP Section
               0.7.2 "NO sys_id literals anywhere"):
        The case's OWN <sys_id> below is the record's primary key,
        which is acceptable per the AAP rule (it is NOT a reference to
        any other record). It is a deterministic 32-character lowercase
        hex value computed at file generation time as the MD5 of the
        idempotent subject "Demo case 04: Pending (General Inquiry)" =
        b75276ffbd2d4b5536d3ab87d5fdeebd - so the Update Set engine
        resolves the same sys_id on every PDI import, making the record
        idempotent.

        EVERY cross-reference field below uses the stable human-readable
        lookup key (user_name / name / scope source) as both the
        display_value attribute AND the text content - NOT a hardcoded
        sys_id literal. This matches the convention established by every
        peer file in the scoped Update Set (sys_user_*, sys_user_group_*,
        sys_user_has_role_*, dictionary/x_[scope]_*, cases 05/06/07/08/
        09/10, etc.) and complies with the AAP Section 0.7.2 "NO sys_id
        literals anywhere" rule:
          - <assigned_agent display_value="x_[scope]_demo_agent">
                x_[scope]_demo_agent
            </assigned_agent>  resolves by user_name lookup
          - <assigned_group display_value="x_[scope]_demo_team">
                x_[scope]_demo_team
            </assigned_group>  resolves by name lookup
          - <sys_scope display_value="Case Management">x_[scope]</sys_scope>
                resolves by scope source-name lookup
          - <sys_package display_value="Case Management" source="x_[scope]">
                x_[scope]
            </sys_package>  resolves by scope source-name lookup

      Rule 8 - Scope binding:
        <sys_scope>   binds this case row to the scoped application via
                      the scope source name "x_[scope]" defined in
                      ../../app/sys_scope/x_[scope].xml at
                      <source>x_[scope]</source>; the display_value
                      "Case Management" matches the sys_app's human-
                      readable name.
        <sys_package> follows the same pattern with the additional
                      source="x_[scope]" attribute that is required by
                      the Update Set engine for scope-package binding.
        Note: the source attribute value "x_[scope]" matches what every
        peer file uses; it is the scope's <source> field, NOT the
        scoped application's sys_update_name. This is the convention
        used consistently across the project's Update Set artifacts
        (cases 05/06/07/08/09/10, all sys_user_*, sys_user_group_*,
        sys_user_has_role_* records use the same convention).

      Rule 9 - Idempotency anchor:
        The case's idempotent key is <subject> =
        "Demo case 04: Pending (General Inquiry)". The companion seed
        script ../../scripts/seed_demo_data.js ensureCase() helper
        queries x_[scope]_case by subject BEFORE inserting; the
        action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE" attribute on the inner <x_[scope]_case>
        element ensures the same behavior at Update Set import time.
        Both the action attribute and the deterministic sys_id make
        re-imports on a fresh PDI byte-identical and collision-free.

      Rule 10 - Scoped Update Set XML conventions:
        Root element:  <record_update table="x_[scope]_case">
        Inner element: <x_[scope]_case action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"> for
                       idempotent re-import per AAP Section 0.7.1
                       round-trip-verification gate (Validation Gate 7).
        UTF-8 encoding declared in XML prolog.
        Element ordering: alphabetical (matching the established peer
        convention used by sys_user_*, sys_user_group_*,
        sys_user_has_role_*, role records, cases 05/06/07/08/09/10, and
        dictionary entries across the scoped Update Set). This case
        uniquely contains a <pending_reason> element which sits
        alphabetically between <description> and <priority> in the
        ordering (d < pe < pr).
        Unix-style line endings (LF) per AAP file authoring conventions.

    Source-side semantic reference (read-only, NOT byte-for-byte ported)
    per AAP Section 0.8.1:
      acm-plugins/acm-default-plugins/acm-case-file-plugin/src/main/java/
        com/armedia/acm/plugins/casefile/model/CaseFile.java
        ArkCase's CaseFile JPA entity declares ~80 fields including
        cm_case_status (the source for our <status>), cm_case_priority
        (the source for our <priority>), cm_case_type (the source for
        our <type>), cm_case_title (the source for our <subject>),
        cm_case_details (Lob; the source for our <description>), and
        the queue/response timing fields (cm_response_due_date, etc.)
        that informed the Pending/Awaiting-Info semantics. The
        ServiceNow target collapses ArkCase's ~80 fields to the user-
        prompt's 12-field schema (number, type, status, priority,
        subject, description, opened_date, closed_date, assigned_group,
        assigned_agent, requester_name, requester_email - plus the
        optional pending_reason). ArkCase's ChangeCaseFileStateService
        Java class (which managed status transitions and is the source
        of the In Progress -> Pending and Pending -> In Progress
        semantics) is replaced in this POC by Flow Designer's
        general_inquiry_state_machine.xml flow plus its
        validate_pending_transition subflow and the
        clear_pending_reason_on_inprogress business rule. ArkCase did
        not have a direct equivalent of the pending_reason field; that
        field was synthesized in this POC from the user prompt's
        explicit requirement (AAP Section 0.5.5) for a reason-capture
        on the In Progress -> Pending transition.

    Validation hooks (per the agent prompt):
      - The XML well-formedness check (xmllint with no-output flag)
        returns zero errors.
      - No-PII grep returns zero matches against (john|jane|smith|doe|
        @gmail|@yahoo|@outlook|@hotmail|\.com|\.org|\.net) - the
        synthetic identifiers ("Synthetic Requester Four",
        "requester-4@example.invalid", "x_[scope]_demo_agent",
        "x_[scope]_demo_team", "Awaiting Info") do not include any
        PII tokens.
      - Choice-value validation: <type>General Inquiry</type>,
        <status>Pending</status>, <priority>High</priority>,
        <pending_reason>Awaiting Info</pending_reason> - capital G/I,
        capital P, capital H, capital A/I respectively.
      - Anti-pattern validation: NO <number>, NO <opened_date>,
        NO <closed_date> elements present; <pending_reason> IS
        present and contains exactly "Awaiting Info".
      - Sys-id-literal validation: only ONE <sys_id> element (the
        case's own primary key); NO sys_id literals appear in any
        cross-reference field.
      - Scope-placeholder validation: the literal `[scope]` placeholder
        is preserved verbatim in the sys_class_name, sys_update_name,
        all reference values, and the file path; the PDI auto-assigns
        the actual concrete scope id at App Engine Studio creation
        time, and the Update-Set apply-time substitution propagates
        consistently across all bracketed placeholders.

    Key insights (per the agent prompt):
      1. Demo case 04 is the canonical Pending case for the General
         Inquiry flow AND for the entire 10-case dataset. It is the
         ONLY Pending case in the dataset, occupying the Pending slot
         alone in the status coverage matrix.
      2. The <pending_reason> field IS REQUIRED for Pending status.
         Per AAP Section 0.5.5, the In Progress -> Pending transition
         sets pending_reason from the choice list. The Pending -> In
         Progress transition (handled by the
         clear_pending_reason_on_inprogress business rule) clears it.
         Pending is the ONLY status that carries pending_reason; cases
         01 (Draft), 02 (Open), 03 (In Progress), 05 (Resolved), 06
         (Closed), 07 (Open), 08 (In Progress), 09 (Resolved), and
         10 (Closed) all have pending_reason absent/unpopulated.
      3. The choice value "Awaiting Info" is one of three registered
         choices in ../../choices/sys_choice_case_pending_reason.xml.
         The other two are "Awaiting Third Party" and "Other". Demo
         case 04 uses "Awaiting Info" because it is the most common
         pause reason (clarifying information from the requester or
         another party) and it is the FIRST choice in the registered
         alphabetical order, exercising the simplest/canonical case.
      4. The status "Pending" has a capital P. Not lowercase, not all
         caps. The exact choice value is "Pending" per AAP Section
         0.5.7 and ../../choices/sys_choice_case_status.xml.
      5. The validation chain that allows Pending: (1) the case has
         assigned_group set (was set on Draft -> Open transition),
         (2) the case has assigned_agent set (was set on Open -> In
         Progress transition), (3) the agent is a member of the group
         (validated by the validate_assigned_agent_membership
         business rule), (4) pending_reason is set on the In Progress
         -> Pending transition (set by the validate_pending_transition
         subflow). All four conditions hold for this case.
      6. Demo case 04 has one Open task per the seed script's task
         table: "Demo task 03: Follow up with requester" (Open, +2
         days due_date). This task supports the Pending semantics:
         the case is paused, but a follow-up task is still tracked
         for the agent. Like case 03 (which is BLOCKED from resolving
         by an Open task), this case would also be blocked from
         resolving until the task is closed; however, this case is
         in Pending not In Progress, so the resolve attempt would
         only trigger after the case returns to In Progress.
      7. Demo case 04 has one Person-type Witness party (referencing
         the demo agent) per the seed script's party table. This
         exercises the Person branch of the polymorphic UI Policy on
         the case_party form (the
         x_[scope]_case_party_conditional_fields UI Policy shows the
         person reference field when party_type=Person and hides the
         organization reference field).
      8. The case appears in the Agent Workspace dashboard's "My
         Open Cases" list. The list filter is "status NOT IN
         (Resolved, Closed) AND assigned_agent =
         javascript:gs.getUserID()". Pending is NOT in the exclusion
         set, and the demo agent is the assigned_agent; when the
         demo agent impersonates and opens the dashboard, this case
         shows in the list. This case also populates the SOLE
         Pending slice in the case_count_by_status donut and the
         SOLE Pending bar in the all_cases_by_status bar chart.
      9. The <pending_reason> element placement is critical. Per
         ServiceNow's XML serialization convention (alphabetical),
         it sits between <description> and <priority>. The element
         ordering in this file (with pending_reason inserted) is:
         assigned_agent, assigned_group, description, pending_reason,
         priority, requester_email, requester_name, status, subject,
         sys_class_name, sys_created_by, sys_id, sys_package,
         sys_scope, sys_update_name, type. This matches the strict
         alphabetical convention used by every peer case file.
     10. The avg_time_to_close widget excludes this case. Pending
         cases are not Closed, so they do not contribute to the
         average-time-to-close calculation. Only cases 06 (Closed
         General Inquiry) and 10 (Closed Complaint) drive that
         widget. This case does, however, contribute to the
         cases_opened_30d single-score widget (since the
         set_opened_date business rule auto-sets opened_date to
         "now" at insert time, placing this case in the 30-day
         window) and to the case_count_by_status donut (Pending
         slice).
-->
<record_update table="x_[scope]_case">
    <x_[scope]_case action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE">
        <assigned_agent display_value="x_[scope]_demo_agent">x_[scope]_demo_agent</assigned_agent>
        <assigned_group display_value="x_[scope]_demo_team">x_[scope]_demo_team</assigned_group>
        <description>Synthetic Pending case awaiting external info.</description>
        <pending_reason>Awaiting Info</pending_reason>
        <priority>High</priority>
        <requester_email>requester-4@example.invalid</requester_email>
        <requester_name>Synthetic Requester Four</requester_name>
        <status>Pending</status>
        <subject>Demo case 04: Pending (General Inquiry)</subject>
